                    "company": "Dutch Research Institute for Transitions (DRIFT)",
                    "description": "TRANSIT (TRANsformative Social Innovation Theory) is an ambitious research project that will develop a theory of transformative social innovation which is about empowerment and change in society. It is co-funded by the European Commission and runs for four years, from January 2014 until December 2017. TRANSIT utilizes a research method which encourages feedback from social entrepreneurs and innovators, policy makers and academics to develop a theory with practical relevance.\n\nI was specifically involved in:\nCase study research on Impact Hub Rotterdam, Amsterdam and Impact Hub Global (interviews, reporting & helping with analysis)\nCo-organizing and documenting an academic workshop with scholars from around the world. \nCo-organizing and documenting TRANSIT project meeting with all consortium partners\nWriting case-study reports of Impact Hubs (Global, Amsterdam, Rotterdam) and Ecovillage Network (case: Tamera in Portugal)\nWriting report on Transition Academy workshop: Transition Theory and Permaculture",
