                    "company": "Maastricht University Green Office",
                    "description": "As part of my work for the Green Office, the official sustainability department of Maastricht University, I was promoting and coordinating sustainability research for students and staff at the university. Bridging gaps between disciplines and faculties, as well as between the academia and society was a main orientation of my work, inspired by inter- and transdisciplinary research. \n\nSpecifically, I developed a Living Laboratory program, whereby students get the possibility to research on real-life sustainability challenges of stakeholders within and outside the university and thereby to support the change-making efforts of these actors. \n\nAdditionally, I organized symposia for researchers to develop a knowledge network that fosters inter-disciplinary research and knowledge exchange across UM faculties, addressing the grand challenges of the 21st century. \n\nFinally, I coordinated the Maastricht University Journal of Sustainability Studies, which offers students the possibility to publish their sustainability-related papers and theses in a peer-reviewed academic journal.",
